{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01QvNQbojXrvpXrLT4pZpBzp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The 3-node CockroachDB cluster is fully deployed and healthy. Here's a summary of what was deployed and the key issue encountered:\n\n**Resources created:**\n- `Service/crdb-cluster` — headless service (DNS for pod-to-pod discovery), with `publishNotReadyAddresses: true`\n- `Service/crdb-cluster-public` — public ClusterIP service for client access\n- `StatefulSet/crdb-cluster` — 3 replicas, `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0`, insecure mode, 10Gi PVC per pod\n- `PodDisruptionBudget/crdb-cluster-pdb` — `minAvailable: 2` to preserve quorum\n\n**Key issue resolved:** The headless service needs `publishNotReadyAddresses: true`. Without it, Kubernetes only publishes DNS for Ready pods, causing a deadlock — pods can't become Ready because they can't resolve each other's hostnames, because they're not Ready yet. After patching the service, all three nodes came up within ~30 seconds.\n\n`cockroach init` was also required to bootstrap the cluster after pod-0 started (standard CockroachDB procedure — nodes wait for init before accepting connections)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":960,"cache_read_input_tokens":46340,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":960},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d87f3a41-4941-46a1-9f2b-c0d2057237f2","uuid":"daed2534-1d4f-46d1-ab01-b60e74eec390","request_id":"req_011CcfBEoGU5hStLma99GD2o"}
